6. Configure TLS for Stock Service (Internal Encryption)
First we secure stock microservice.
________________________________________
Add Service Annotation
Edit:
stock-service.yaml
Add:
annotations:
  service.beta.openshift.io/serving-cert-secret-name: stock-service-cert
Full example:
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: stock
  namespace: network-review
  annotations:
    service.beta.openshift.io/serving-cert-secret-name: stock-service-cert
________________________________________
What This Annotation Does
It tells OpenShift:
Generate TLS certificate for this service
OpenShift Service CA controller will:
1.	generate certificate
2.	sign with cluster CA
3.	create secret
stock-service-cert
________________________________________
Apply the Service
oc apply -f stock-service.yaml
________________________________________
7. Verify Certificate
Command:
oc get secret stock-service-cert \
--output="jsonpath={.data.tls\.crt}" \
| base64 -d | openssl x509 -text
________________________________________
Command Breakdown
Get certificate
oc get secret stock-service-cert
Retrieve TLS secret.
________________________________________
Extract TLS cert
jsonpath={.data.tls\.crt}
Extract:
tls.crt
________________________________________
Decode base64
Secrets are stored encoded.
base64 -d
Decodes certificate.
________________________________________
Inspect certificate
openssl x509 -text
Shows certificate details.
________________________________________
Important Output
DNS:stock.network-review.svc
DNS:stock.network-review.svc.cluster.local
These are internal DNS names.
________________________________________
8. Configure TLS in Stock Deployment
Now the application must use the certificate.
Edit:
stock-deployment.yaml
________________________________________
Mount the Secret
volumeMounts:
- name: stock-service-cert
  mountPath: /etc/pki/stock/
Volumes:
volumes:
- name: stock-service-cert
  secret:
    secretName: stock-service-cert
________________________________________
Result
Inside container:
/etc/pki/stock/tls.crt
/etc/pki/stock/tls.key
Application uses them.
________________________________________
9. Enable TLS in Application
Environment variable:
env:
- name: TLS_ENABLED
  value: "true"
This tells the application:
start HTTPS server
________________________________________
10. Update Health Probes
Health probes must use HTTPS.
readinessProbe:
  httpGet:
    port: 8085
    path: /readyz
    scheme: HTTPS
livenessProbe:
  httpGet:
    port: 8085
    path: /livez
    scheme: HTTPS
________________________________________
11. Apply Deployment
oc apply -f stock-deployment.yaml
Deployment restarts.
Pods now run HTTPS server.
________________________________________
