13. Configure Product to Trust Stock TLS
Stock certificate is signed by OpenShift internal CA.
Product must trust it.
________________________________________
Create CA ConfigMap
Edit:
service-ca-configmap.yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: service-ca
  namespace: network-review
  annotations:
    service.beta.openshift.io/inject-cabundle: "true"
________________________________________
What This Does
OpenShift injects cluster CA certificate.
Creates:
service-ca.crt
________________________________________
Apply:
oc create -f service-ca-configmap.yaml
________________________________________
14. Verify CA Injection
oc describe configmap service-ca
Look for:
service-ca.crt
________________________________________
15. Configure Product Deployment
Edit:
product-deployment.yaml
Add environment variables:
env:
- name: CERT_CA
  value: "/etc/pki/ca-trust/extracted/pem/tls-ca-bundle.pem"
This tells application where CA certificate is.
________________________________________
Update Stock URL
- name: STOCK_URL
  value: "https://stock.network-review.svc"
Now product uses HTTPS.
________________________________________
16. Mount CA Bundle
volumeMounts:
- name: trusted-ca
  mountPath: /etc/pki/ca-trust/extracted/pem
Volume:
volumes:
- name: trusted-ca
  configMap:
    name: service-ca
________________________________________
Apply deployment:
oc apply -f product-deployment.yaml
________________________________________
17. Test Internal TLS
Run:
oc exec deployment/product \
-- curl -s https://stock.network-review.svc/product/1
Output:
10
Meaning:
product -> stock communication works via HTTPS
