18. Configure External TLS for Product
External users must access:
https://product.apps.ocp4.example.com
But we use corporate CA certificate.
________________________________________
Create TLS Secret
oc create secret tls passthrough-cert \
--cert certs/product.pem \
--key certs/product.key
Explanation:
Option	Meaning
secret tls	create TLS secret
--cert	certificate file
--key	private key
________________________________________
19. Mount Certificate in Product Pod
volumeMounts:
- name: passthrough-cert
  mountPath: /etc/pki/product/
Volume:
volumes:
- name: passthrough-cert
  secret:
    secretName: passthrough-cert
________________________________________
20. Enable TLS in Product
env:
- name: TLS_ENABLED
  value: "true"
________________________________________
Update probes:
scheme: HTTPS
________________________________________
Apply:
oc apply -f product-deployment.yaml
________________________________________
21. Create Passthrough Route
Command:
oc create route passthrough product-https \
--service product \
--port 8080 \
--hostname product.apps.ocp4.example.com
________________________________________
Route Explanation
Field	Meaning
passthrough	TLS goes directly to pod
service product	backend service
port 8080	container port
hostname	external DNS
Flow:
Client -> Router -> Pod
Router does NOT terminate TLS.
________________________________________
22. Test External Access
curl --cacert certs/ca.pem \
https://product.apps.ocp4.example.com/products
Output:
[{"id":1,"name":"rpi4_4gb","stock":10}]
